# CHIMERA NEXUS - Windows Installation Troubleshooting

## ‚ùå Problem: "Microsoft Visual C++ 14.0 or greater is required"

This happens when trying to install scikit-learn from source.

### ‚úÖ Solution 1: Use Quick Fix Installer (RECOMMENDED)
```powershell
.\install_quick_windows.ps1
```
This installs specific package versions with pre-built wheels (no compilation needed).

### ‚úÖ Solution 2: Install Build Tools (if you want latest versions)
1. Download: https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/visual-cpp-build-tools/
2. Install "Desktop development with C++"
3. Restart PowerShell
4. Run: `.\install_nexus.ps1`

### ‚úÖ Solution 3: Manual Installation
```powershell
# Activate environment
.\droxai-env\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# Install specific working versions
pip install "tensorflow==2.16.1"
pip install "scikit-learn==1.4.0"
pip install boto3 openai-whisper pyttsx3
```

## ‚ùå Problem: "Unable to create process using..." (pip launcher error)

This is a virtual environment path issue (DroxAI vs Drox_AI).

### ‚úÖ Solution: Use python -m pip
```powershell
# Instead of: pip install <package>
# Use:
python -m pip install <package>

# Or recreate environment:
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force droxai-env
python -m venv droxai-env
.\droxai-env\Scripts\Activate.ps1
```

## ‚ùå Problem: "dependency resolver backtracking" (taking forever)

### ‚úÖ Solution: Use requirements_windows.txt
```powershell
pip install -r requirements_windows.txt
```

Or install in stages:
```powershell
# Stage 1: Core
pip install websockets aiosqlite numpy pyyaml

# Stage 2: ML (specific versions)
pip install "tensorflow==2.16.1" "scikit-learn==1.4.0"

# Stage 3: Optional
pip install boto3 openai-whisper pyttsx3
```

## ‚ùå Problem: PyAudio not installing

### ‚úÖ Solution: Download pre-built wheel
1. Go to: https://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#pyaudio
2. Download: `PyAudio‚Äë0.2.14‚Äëcp312‚Äëcp312‚Äëwin_amd64.whl`
3. Install:
   ```powershell
   pip install C:\Users\<YourName>\Downloads\PyAudio-0.2.14-cp312-cp312-win_amd64.whl
   ```

Alternative: Use sounddevice (already installed)
```python
import sounddevice as sd  # Instead of pyaudio
```

## ‚ùå Problem: TensorFlow not finding GPU

### ‚úÖ Solution: Install CUDA-enabled version
```powershell
pip uninstall tensorflow
pip install tensorflow[and-cuda]
```

Verify GPU:
```powershell
python -c "import tensorflow as tf; logging.info(tf.config.list_physical_devices('GPU'))"
```

## ‚ùå Problem: "cannot import name 'XXX' from 'sklearn'"

### ‚úÖ Solution: Force reinstall
```powershell
pip uninstall scikit-learn
pip install --no-cache-dir "scikit-learn==1.4.0"
```

